5 years ago I set out to become a YouTuber with a goal to be able to get paid to travel the world. At the time, with 0 subscribers, barely any money, this felt like a near impossible goal. I recall even telling myself - if I can figure out how to do this, I will never doubt myself about anything.. A couple years later I’ve been able to travel to 50+ countries, work with my favorite brands, and make a living that supports myself and even others. Moral of the story, making that initial goal for myself, has truly now given me confidence for future goals when the going gets tough.

social_posts.post_text: My favorite trip from 2023 🇱🇦

We all have to start somewhere.
My first YouTube video was filmed in my Mom’s laundry room on a $88 camera. I was also teased by many friends for trying to do it since it wasn’t “cool” at the time. Reflecting back now, I’m just grateful I didn’t listen to anyone but my gut. For anyone who’s contemplating starting a new chapter, get out and get busy.

#EGPartner As an @expedia member I can save 10% or more on over 100,000 hotels worldwide with Member Prices, making me enjoy experiences like staying on a private island that much sweeter 👌🏽 link to book in bio
maybe @barbaracorcoran can help me out with that last one..
DIML🗽

2023 was an unbelievable year for my career. Got 34M+ views on YouTube, starred in a Korean commercial, filmed in 15 countries, dream partnership with @expedia , surpassed financial goals.. The thing I’m most proud of though, is prioritizing my health and wellness. Discovering my love for running and going from never running more than a 5k in my life to being able to run a marathon has changed my life. My #1 goal for 2023 was to get in the best shape of my life and I can confidently say that goal was achieved. 
p.s. @expedia if it weren’t for my health you would be first 😉❤️
